Set

Source: R/0-SetR6.R
Set.Rd

The Set() is considered and implemented as a specialized Container(), that is, elements are always unique in the Container() and it provides typical set operations such as union and intersect.

Details

Under the hood, elements of a set object are stored in a hash-table and sorted by their length and, in case of ties, by their lexicographical representation.

See also

Container(), set()
